<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-35-1194 </DOCNO><TEXT>United States strategic forces are primarily intended to deter the SovietUnion from initiating a nuclear war. To do so, U.S. policy calls forthem to be able to survive a Soviet nuclear strike and retaliate in anappropriate and timely manner. Since the 1960s, the Soviets have upgradedand significantly expanded the capabilities of their strategic forces.The Administration believes that, in response, the United States mustincrease not only the numbers of its forces and their chance of survivinga Soviet strike, but also their destructive capability, endurance, andresponsiveness.</TEXT></DOC>